reviews.text: Went to collect pre paid tickets, people outside smoking, drinking and swearing, not nice. Was better in the morning but a very drab place

It's a small railway station, what more can be said? Today we were dropping off someone, sometimes we pick people up. Parking never a real problem, but we don't visit during rush hours, always convienient. Today a partially sighted man was catching a train, the station employee walked over to him and supported him while entering the train. Part of his job, I know, but still good to see.
Safe, friendly taxi's available from the taxi rank outside the station.
This is my favourite railway station in Cosham. It has trains you can get on and off, which is useful if you want to go to Cosham and come home again.
Easy access from A27, so very convenient for pick up/drop off. Otherwise, it's just another station.
